The paper discusses the use of robots in real-world environments, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The paper also discusses the use of human knowledge to improve robotic control, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper proposes a framework for learning and generalization of primitive skills, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of vision in robotic manipulation, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed framework on a humanoid robot, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY).
